	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: secondary</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 31st 11:08 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=125152><span id= >Rollander</span></a><br><span id=notbold>485 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.95]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Never put a 1hs in your PRIMARY.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can't BS with a slashing weapon in primary.  The only time you should ever put a 1hs in your primary to increase your skill quickly (1 1hs in each hand, or 1hb, or whatever)<br><br>Personally, I recommend using a Piercer Primary and 1hs Offhand, because it opens a lot more opportunities for better weapons.  (most piercers are kinda crappy IMO, and slashers are generally more plentiful and cheaper)<br><br>Once you get above 50, your piercing skill will surpass your slashing, and unless you have a really nice 1hs in your offhand, go to a piercer in each hand.</p>&nbsp;<br>-------------------------<br>Rogues do it from behind.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276</a> <br>Tyrlinoth Arkonnen &lt;Brothers of Darkness&gt; - EQ's Drunkest Guild<br>The Nameless</td></td></tr>
